– 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D98799A46EFFA8FCD7FAE4FAF0F80F:8EAF6054A46EFFA8FC56F965FC5FF942" box="[928,974,1724,1748]" country="Paraguay" name="This" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">This</location>
species was known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1249,1346,1725,1749]" name="Paraguay" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TAYLOR" firstAuthor="TAYLOR" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR, 2005</bibRefCitation>
) and has recently also been confirmed from eastern and northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[942,1005,1790,1814]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(e.g., 
<emphasis box="[1068,1236,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">Kuhlmann 3958</emphasis>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1247,1295,1790,1814]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15859" name="Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" type="Herbarium">MO</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1347,1378,1790,1814]" country="Brazil" name="Instituto de Botânica" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" type="Herbarium">SP</collectionCode>
; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">
Stannard et al. 
<accessionNumber box="[912,1000,1823,1847]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/H51938" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">
<collectionCode box="[912,933,1823,1847]" country="Finland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" type="Herbarium">H</collectionCode>
51938
</accessionNumber>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1012,1062,1823,1847]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15859" name="Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" type="Herbarium">MO</collectionCode>
). Four duplicates of the type collection of 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1078,1856,1880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rudgea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hassleriana">
<emphasis box="[881,1078,1856,1880]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">Rudgea hassleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are deposited at 
<collectionCode box="[1263,1285,1856,1880]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="15" pageNumber="304" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
, where Chodat worked. The only specimen in his personal herbarium has original drawings and is here considered the 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1373,1921,1945]" pageId="15" pageNumber="304">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
